label: NetworkNode
description: Represents a physical or logical entity within the network, such as a cell site, base station, or user equipment.

label: ProtocolMessage
description: A message exchanged between network entities, carrying information about network operations.

label: Timer
description: A time-based event that triggers a specific action or state transition.

label: Procedure
description: A sequence of steps or actions that define a specific network operation.

label: UserState
description: The current state of a user or device within the network.
